The paper deals with the problem of automated team formation, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus on team cohesion and performance suggests a potential connection to social and information networks (cs.SI). The use of measures and optimization techniques implies a connection to machine learning (cs.LG) and cybernetics (cs.CY). Finally, the emphasis on team characteristics and performance could also suggest a connection to human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
